## 🔴 Section 1: Remaining Critical Bugs

### Bug 1: ⚠️ Hardcoded Private Key Still in Repository

**File:** [deploy-wsl.sh](file:///c:/Users/BMSIT/ShadowVault/scripts/deploy-wsl.sh#L9)

```bash
PRIVATE_KEY="APrivateKey1zkpBNfBdXXqjKoGq66PhJANkwbmtX5Pm19BqnwLnVMiFuJX"
```

> [!CAUTION]
> This private key is **still hardcoded in plain text**. Anyone who sees this repo can drain the wallet. Even if you remove it now, it's in your git history forever.

**Fix needed:**
1. Remove the key from the script
2. Use `$PRIVATE_KEY` environment variable only
3. Run `git filter-branch` or `git-filter-repo` to purge from history
4. **Rotate the key** — generate a new one and transfer any funds

---

### Bug 2: ⚠️ Old Empty Route Directories Create Routing Conflicts

The old route directories still exist alongside the new [(app)/](file:///c:/Users/BMSIT/ShadowVault/app/api/upload/route.ts#5-49) route group:

| Old (empty) Directory | Conflict With |
|---|---|
| `app/dashboard/` (empty) | `app/(app)/dashboard/page.tsx` |
| `app/marketplace/` (empty) | `app/(app)/marketplace/page.tsx` |
| `app/files/[id]/` (empty) | `app/(app)/files/[id]/page.tsx` |
| `app/my-files/` (empty) | `app/(app)/my-files/page.tsx` |
| `app/purchased/` (empty) | `app/(app)/purchased/page.tsx` |
| `app/settings/` (empty) | `app/(app)/settings/page.tsx` |
| `app/upload/` (missing) | `app/(app)/upload/page.tsx` |

> [!WARNING]
> While empty directories alone won't create active routes, Next.js can behave unpredictably with conflicting route structures. **Delete all old empty directories** to avoid confusion and potential build issues.

---

### Bug 3: ⚠️ `.env.example` Is Gitignored

**File:** [.gitignore](file:///c:/Users/BMSIT/ShadowVault/.gitignore#L18)

```gitignore
.env.example
```

`.env.example` is the **template** file that tells new developers which env vars are needed. It should **NOT** be gitignored — it contains no secrets, only placeholder values. If you push this, new contributors can't set up the project.

**Fix:** Remove `.env.example` from `.gitignore`.

---

### Bug 4: ⚠️ `validateEnv()` Is Never Actually Called

**File:** [lib/env.ts](file:///c:/Users/BMSIT/ShadowVault/lib/env.ts)

The function exists but is never imported or called anywhere in the app. Missing env vars will just silently use empty strings.

**Fix:** Call `validateEnv()` in `(app)/layout.tsx` or the API route to surface errors early.

---

### Bug 5: ⚠️ `cidToField` Is Now Async But Upload Uses `await`

**File:** [upload/page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/BMSIT/ShadowVault/app/%28app%29/upload/page.tsx#L38)

```typescript
const fieldValue = await cidToField(cid); // ✅ correct, uses await
```

This is fine currently, but note that `cidToField()` uses `crypto.subtle.digest()` which is **only available in secure contexts** (HTTPS or localhost). If deployed behind a non-HTTPS reverse proxy, it will fail silently.

