## 🔒 Section 3: Security Review

### Still Vulnerable

| Issue | Severity | Detail |
|---|---|---|
| **Private key in git history** | 🔴 CRITICAL | Even if you remove it now, it's in commit history |
| **No rate limiting on `/api/upload`** | ⚠️ HIGH | Anyone can spam your Pinata account through the API |
| **No authentication on `/api/upload`** | ⚠️ HIGH | The upload endpoint has no wallet signature verification — anyone can POST |
| **`localStorage` metadata** | ⚠️ HIGH | CID, IV, salt, filename still localStorage only. Clear browser = files unrecoverable |
| **No CORS configuration** | ⚠️ MEDIUM | API route has no origin restriction |
| **`NEXT_PUBLIC_PINATA_JWT_TOKEN` fallback** | ⚠️ MEDIUM | The API route tries `process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_PINATA_JWT_TOKEN` as fallback — this would expose JWT client-side |

### Fixed ✅

| Issue | Resolution |
|---|---|
| IPFS keys client-side | Server-side API route (`/api/upload`) |
| No address validation | `isValidAleoAddress()` with regex |
| No file size limits | 50MB max enforced |
| No error boundary | `ErrorBoundary` component wrapping providers |

